Summarizing overview information

Source: R/overview.R
summary.overview.Rd

print and summary method for "overview" class.

# S3 method for overview
summary(object, ...)

Arguments

object

an object of class "overview", usually, a result of a call to overview().
...

further arguments passed to or from other methods.

Details

summary.overview() tries to be smart about formatting 14 information of overview.

See also

overview, plot.overview.

Examples

# \donttest{
ov <- overview(jobchange)
ov
#>     division        metrics   value
#> 1       size   observations   19158
#> 2       size      variables      14
#> 3       size         values  268212
#> 4       size    memory_size 2318464
#> 5    missing   complete_obs    8955
#> 6    missing    missing_obs   10203
#> 7    missing   missing_vars       8
#> 8    missing missing_values   20733
#> 9  data_type       numerics       1
#> 10 data_type       integers       1
#> 11 data_type        factors       7
#> 12 data_type     characters       1
#> 13 data_type         others       4
